35. Rxg7+ $18) 34. Nxd7 $16) 25... bxa2 $2 ({More tenacious was} 25... Kh8 26.
Bg5 Bxg5 27. Rxg5 bxa2 28. Rg4 Nb3 29. Rxa2 a5 {White's position is preferable,
but there is still a lot to play for.}) 26. Qg3 Bf8 27. Nf4 {[%cal Gf4h5]} Kh8
28. Nh5 g6 29. Bg5 ({Equally good was} 29. Bxf8 Raxf8 30. Nf6 Rg7 31. Rxa2 Nc6
32. h4 {[%cal Gh4h5] With a great White advantage.}) 29... Be8 30. Bf6+ Kg8 31.
Nf4 {[%csl Re6,Rg6][%cal Gf4g6,Gf4e6]} Rb7 32. Rxa2 $18 Bb4 33. Ra1 Nb3 34. Rd1
Bf7 35. h4 Nxd4 36. Nxg6 hxg6 37. Rdxd4 1-0

