minimal advantage.} Qxe4 18. Bxe4 Bb7 19. Rd7 Rab8 20. Rxb7 Rxb7 21. Bxc6 Rc7
22. Bf3 Rxc3 23. Bd2 $14 {With a slight advantage in the endgame.}) 15. h4 (15.
Re1 b5 16. h4 Bb7 17. h5 Rac8 18. hxg6 fxg6 19. Bh6 Rf7 20. a4 $14 {Opening a
new front. White's position is slightly preferable.}) 15... Bd7 (15... b5 16.
h5 Bb7 17. Re1 Rfd8 18. Be4 Rab8 19. Bf4 Rd7 20. Qe3 Na5 21. Ng5 Nc4 22. Qh3
Bxg5 23. Bxg5 Qxe5 24. Qh4 $36 {With considerable pressure on the black king
for the sacrificed pawn.}) 16. h5 ({Even more exact was} 16. Bh6 $1 Rfd8 17.
Qe3 Be8 18. h5 Rd5 19. Re1 Rad8 {[%csl Rd3]} 20. Bf1 {White removes his
light-squared bishop from the d-file where it needed to be defended.} Qa5 21.
Rac1 Qxa2 22. Qf4 Qa5 23. hxg6 hxg6 24. Bg5 Bxg5 25. Qxg5 Qa3 26. Qh4 $40 {
[%csl Rf6,Rh7][%cal Gf3g5,Gh4h7,Gg5e4,Ge4f6] The white attack is becoming more
serious.}) 16... Rfd8 17. Bf4 ({Another possibility was} 17. Bh6 Be8 18. Re1
