(16... Qc7 $2 17. Ng5 {[%csl Re6,Rf7][%cal Gf4f7]} f5 18. Nxe6 Bxe6 19. Bxe6+ {
With a great white advantage.}) 17. Re1 {[%csl Ye5][%cal Ge1e5] Releasing the
knight from the defence of the e5-pawn.} Be8 18. Ng5 Qxc3 19. Nxe6 $1 Nd4 {
The best defensive resource.} (19... fxe6 $4 20. Bxe6+ Kh8 21. Bg5 $18) 20.
Nxd8 Qxc4 21. Nxb7 Ne2+ 22. Rxe2 Qxe2 23. Nd6 $16 {With an advantage for White.
}) 16... Qxd8 (16... Nxd8 $2 17. Rd1 Qa4 18. Rd4 Bd7 19. Bb3 Qc6 20. Qf4 Be8
21. Bg5 Qc7 22. Bxe7 Qxe7 23. Ng5 $40 {[%csl Re6][%cal Gg5e4,Ge4f6,Gh2h4,Gd4d6]
With a powerful white attack.}) 17. Qf4 Qc7 ({Other alternatives also fail to
reduce White's initiative on the kingside:} 17... Bd7 18. Ng5 Be8 19. Re1 Ra7
20. Bb3 b5 21. h4 $16 {[%csl Re6][%cal Gg5e4,Gh4h5]}) (17... b5 18. Ng5 Bxg5
19. Bxg5 Qe8 20. Bh6 f5 21. Bb3 $16 {[%cal Ga1d1,Gd1d6,Gh2h4]}) 18. Rd1 $6 ({
To a great advantage leads} 18. h4 $1 Na5 19. Bf1 b5 20. Rd1 Bb7 21. Ng5 f6 22.
Nxh7 $1 Qxe5 (22... Kxh7 $4 23. Bg7 $3 $18 {[%csl Rc7][%cal Ge5f6,Gf4h6,Rh7g7,
Gf4c7] A Brilliant move with which White is winning.}) 23. Rd7 Qxf4 24. Bxf4
Kxh7 25. Rxe7+ Kg8 26. Bd3 $16 {And the black position collapses.}) 18... Bd7 (
{Weaker is} 18... f6 $2 19. exf6 Qxf4 20. fxe7 $1 Qxh6 (20... Qf7 $4 21. Rd8+
$18) 21. e8=Q+ Qf8 22. Bxe6+ Kg7 23. Qxf8+ Kxf8 24. Bd5 $16 {With an extra
pawn in the endgame.}) 19. Ng5 (19. h4 $5) 19... Be8 20. Rd6 ({An excellent
example of White's resources in this type of structure is the following
variation.} 20. Re1 $5 Na5 (20... b5 21. Bb3 b4 22. cxb4 Rd8 23. a3 a5 24. Bxe6
Bxg5 25. Bxg5 fxe6 26. Bxd8 Qxd8 27. h3 $14) 21. Ne4 $1 {A piece sacrifice for
an attack on the black king.} Qxc4 22. Nf6+ Kh8 23. Re4 Qd3 24. h3 {White
needs to spend a tempo against back-rank threats.} Nc6 25. Qh4 {[%csl Rh7]
[%cal Gh6g7,Gh4h7] Threatening checkmate in two moves.} Qd1+ 26. Kh2 Qh5 $8 27.
Bg7+ Kxg7 28. Nxh5+ gxh5 29. Qxh5 $36 {Material is balanced but White still
has the initiative.}) 20... Rd8 $2 ({Black should have continued with} 20...
Qa5 21. Rxe6 fxe6 22. Bxe6+ Kh8 {White has nothing better than to force a draw
with} 23. Qf7 Bxf7 24. Nxf7+ Kg8 25. Nd8+ Kh8 26. Nf7+ $11) 21. Ne4 $18 {
Now White is winning.} f5 (21... Kh8 22. Nf6 Bxd6 23. exd6 Qxd6 24. Bg7+ $1
Kxg7 25. Nxe8+ Rxe8 26. Qxd6 $18) 22. Bxe6+ Kh8 (22... Bf7 23. Bxf7+ Kxf7 24.
Ng5+ Ke8 (24... Bxg5 $4 25. Qc4+ $18) 25. Ne6 Bxd6 26. Nxc7+ Bxc7 27. g3 $18)
23. Bg5 Ra8 24. Bf6+ Bxf6 25. Nxf6 ({More precise and decisive was} 25. exf6
Bf7 (25... fxe4 $4 26. Qh6 $18) 26. Bxf7 Qxf7 27. Ng5 Qe8 28. Qd2 $18) 25...
Bf7 (25... Qe7 26. h3 Rd8 27. Qh4 g5 28. Qh6 Bg6 29. Nd5 Qf8 30. Qxg5 $18) 26.
Qh6 ({Faster was} 26. Nd5 Qxd6 27. exd6 Bxe6 28. Nc7 $18) 26... Bxe6 27. Rxe6
Rg8 ({Somewhat more resistance offered} 27... Qg7 28. Qh4 g5 29. Qc4 Nxe5 30.
Qd5 Nc6 31. h3 Rf8 32. Qxf5 $18) 28. Nxg8 Qg7 29. Rd6 1-0

