{Black has just captured the c3-pawn. How can White justify this sacrifice?} 1.
d5 $3 {A surprising second pawn sacrifice, leaving the rook on a1 hanging!}
Qxa1 {The capture of the rook is the critical continuation. Alternatives offer
White an excellent dynamic game without any major concessions.} (1... exd5 2.
Re1+ Kd8 (2... Be6 3. Ng5 Bb4 (3... Qxa1 $4 4. Nxe6 $18) 4. Nxe6 Qxe1+ 5. Qxe1
Bxe1 6. Nc7+ Kd8 7. Nxa8 Bc3 8. Rb1 $16 {It is not apparent how Black is going
to capture the knight on a8}) 3. Rb1 Re8 4. Rxe8+ Bxe8 5. Bb2 $16 {[%csl Rf6,
Rg7] With excellent piece activity for White.}) (1... O-O 2. dxe6 Bxe6 (2... h6
{Avoiding motifs with Bxh7+.} 3. exf7+ Rxf7 4. Rb1 Qc7 5. Qb3 $18 {[%csl Rf7,
Rg8][%cal Gd3g6,Gc1b2] The lack of development will prove fatal for Black.}) 3.
Ng5 g6 4. Rb1 {[%csl Gb7][%cal Gc1b2,Gb1b7]} Qf6 5. Be4 {[%csl Rb7,Rd6][%cal
Gd1d6] Black is unable to contain the threats of his opponent.}) 2. Qb3 {
[%csl Ra8,Rb7][%cal Gc1b2,Gb3b7]} Be5 {[%cal Rc1b2]} (2... Na6 3. Ba3 {[%csl
Ra1][%cal Gf1a1]} Qxf1+ 4. Bxf1 Bxa3 5. Qxa3 {[%cal Gf3e5,Gf1a6,Re8g8,Rh8f8]}
Nc7 6. Qc3 {[%csl Rc7,Rg7][%cal Gc3c7,Gc3g7]} Nxd5 7. Qxg7 $16 {The exposed
situation of the black king offers White an advantage.}) ({A serious error is} 
2... Qf6 $4 3. Bg5 $18) (2... O-O $2 3. Bb2 $16 {White recovers the material,
keeping the initiative.}) 3. Qxb7 O-O (3... Qxa2 4. dxe6 Qxe6 5. Nxe5 O-O 6.
Qe4 $1 {[%csl Rh7][%cal Ge4h7] White wisely chooses to develop his initiative
instead of winning back the sacrificed material.} f5 7. Qd4 $1 {[%csl Rd7,Re6]
[%cal Gd3c4,Gc4g8] The threat from the a2-g8 diagonal causes Black great
damage.} Nc6 8. Qxd7 Qxd7 9. Nxd7 Rfd8 10. Nc5 $16 {[%csl Rf5] The weak black
f5-pawn gives White chances for victory in the endgame.}) 4. Ba3 Qxa2 {This
pawn capture leads to a forced variation.} 5. Bxf8 Qxd5 6. Be4 Qxb7 7. Bxb7 {
[%csl Ra8,Re5][%cal Gf3e5,Gb7a8]} Bc6 8. Bxa8 Bxf3 9. Bxg7 Bxh2+ 10. Kxh2 Bxa8
11. Bh6 $16 {With a white advantage in the endgame due to the bad placement of
the black pieces. The different-coloured bishops favour the player with the
initiative.} *

